Birnin Kebbi – Five suspects including a staff of Usmanu Danfodio UniversitybTeaching Hospital Sokoto (UDUTH) have been arrested by the Department of State Security (DSS) over alleged sale of three children abducted from Zuru in Kebbi. Gov. Atiku Bagudu, who handed over the three children to their parents on Sunday in Birnin Kebbi, named the suspects as Comfort Nwanko of UDUTH, Dorothy Okonkwo, Uchenna Benedict, Helen Samuel and one Moses who lives in Zuru. He said that the three children, including a set of twins were sold in Anambra in connivance with Nwankwo and Moses. Emulate Prophet Muhammad’s lifestyle in promoting peace –Mohammed Bagudu commended the security operatives for tracking and rescuing the children and assured that the suspects would be prosecuted. He urged parents to be vigilante and monitor their children to prevent them from falling victims of abductors. Yusuf Umar and Rabi Kabiru, parents of the abducted children, commended the governor, vigilantes and security agents for rescuing the children who went missing four months ago.(NAN)